1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with decoding of error-correcting codes, which is a topic closely related to information theory. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper describes a new algorithm for decoding codes, which falls under the domain of data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper involves the study of algebraic codes, which is a topic related to discrete mathematics. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the complexity of decoding algebraic codes, which is a topic related to computational complexity. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the decoding of Reed Solomon codes, which are used in control systems and signal processing, making it relevant to the systems and control sub-category.
